WEBVTT

00:09.508 --> 00:11.009
- Are you ready, kids?

00:11.011 --> 00:12.744
All: Aye, aye, captain!

00:12.746 --> 00:14.278
- I can't hear you.

00:14.280 --> 00:16.180
All: Aye, aye, captain!

00:16.181 --> 00:18.616
- ♪ ohh...

00:18.618 --> 00:21.219
♪ who lives in a pineapple
under the sea? ♪

00:21.221 --> 00:22.854
All: Spongebob squarepants!

00:22.856 --> 00:25.289
- ♪ absorbent and yellow
and porous is he ♪

00:25.291 --> 00:26.591
All: Spongebob squarepants!

00:26.593 --> 00:29.293
- ♪ if nautical nonsense
be something you wish ♪

00:29.295 --> 00:30.294
All: Spongebob squarepants!

00:30.296 --> 00:33.064
- ♪ then drop on the deck
and flop like a fish ♪

00:33.066 --> 00:35.199
All: Spongebob squarepants!
- Ready?

00:35.201 --> 00:37.335
All: Spongebob squarepants!

00:37.337 --> 00:39.270
Spongebob squarepants!

00:39.272 --> 00:41.406
Spongebob squarepants!

00:41.408 --> 00:42.640
- Spongebob

00:42.642 --> 00:44.976
Squarepants!

00:44.978 --> 00:47.512
[laughing]

00:47.514 --> 00:49.714
♪

00:49.716 --> 00:51.616
[waves crashing]

00:53.619 --> 00:56.854
[lilting ukulele music]

00:56.856 --> 01:02.760
♪ ♪

01:02.762 --> 01:03.528
[intense music]

01:03.530 --> 01:05.830
- Witnesses are flocking
around the unveiling

01:05.832 --> 01:08.199
Of bikini bottom's
newest bank,

01:08.201 --> 01:10.768
The bank
of bikini bottom bank.

01:10.770 --> 01:12.203
[lively marching music]

01:12.205 --> 01:13.938
- The first 100 customers

01:13.940 --> 01:15.440
Who join
bank of bikini bottom bank

01:15.442 --> 01:18.776
Will receive instant interest
on their deposit.

01:18.778 --> 01:20.478
- Instant interest?

01:20.480 --> 01:23.548
That's practically
giving money away!

01:23.550 --> 01:24.282
Spongebob!

01:24.284 --> 01:25.216
You're in charge
while I run down

01:25.218 --> 01:26.484
To the bank
of bikini bottom bank.

01:26.486 --> 01:29.554
I got to get down there
before they run out of dough!

01:29.556 --> 01:34.192
[car engine revving,
squealing]

01:34.194 --> 01:35.226
[screech]

01:35.228 --> 01:38.029
Money, here I c--
ooh!

01:38.031 --> 01:41.499
[overlapping murmuring]

01:41.501 --> 01:42.533
- [jabbering]

01:42.535 --> 01:45.870
- Thanks for banking
with bank of bikini bottom bank.

01:45.872 --> 01:47.505
And here's
your instant interest.

01:47.507 --> 01:49.173
[cash register ka-ching]

01:49.175 --> 01:51.709
- [jabbers]

01:51.711 --> 01:53.377
[coins jingle]

01:53.379 --> 01:55.113
[jabbers]

01:55.115 --> 01:57.715
- Free moola just for joining?

01:57.717 --> 02:00.184
Yes!
- [groans]

02:00.186 --> 02:03.321
I'm in money heaven!
[laughs]

02:03.323 --> 02:06.090
- Heads up.
We've got a live one.

02:06.092 --> 02:07.225
- Welcome
to bank of bikini--

02:07.227 --> 02:09.827
- Hi. I want
to see all your money.

02:09.829 --> 02:10.461
- Excuse me?

02:10.463 --> 02:12.230
- Show me
where the money lives.

02:12.232 --> 02:13.698
I bet you got a lot.

02:13.700 --> 02:14.732
I'd like to see all of it.

02:14.734 --> 02:17.168
[alarm rings]
I'm a huge fan of money.

02:17.170 --> 02:18.836
Ooh! Oh! Hey! Hey!

02:18.838 --> 02:21.072
Get your hands--
aah!

02:21.074 --> 02:22.039
[clang]

02:22.041 --> 02:25.877
Anchovies.

02:25.879 --> 02:28.146
[sniffing]

02:28.148 --> 02:28.913
Good day, madame.

02:28.915 --> 02:32.717
I would like to take
a look at your safe, please.

02:32.719 --> 02:34.018
- Sure thing, sir.

02:34.020 --> 02:35.486
[alarm rings]

02:35.488 --> 02:37.054
- Not again.

02:37.056 --> 02:38.689
Aah!

02:38.691 --> 02:40.091
[crash]

02:40.093 --> 02:43.861
Scallops.

02:45.964 --> 02:48.032
[falsetto]
good day, gentlemen.

02:48.034 --> 02:49.233
Both: Good day, ma'am.

02:49.235 --> 02:50.601
- Hello young missy.

02:50.603 --> 02:52.069
- Well, hello, ma'am.

02:52.071 --> 02:53.638
How can we help you today?

02:53.640 --> 02:54.972
- So far, so good.

02:54.974 --> 02:55.640
- Ma'am?

02:55.642 --> 02:57.642
- They haven't
thrown me out yet.

02:57.644 --> 02:58.709
- Ma'am?

02:58.711 --> 03:01.345
- It's all
coming together now.

03:01.347 --> 03:02.446
- Can I help you, ma'am?

03:02.448 --> 03:04.615
A withdrawal? A transfer?

03:04.617 --> 03:05.816
Anything?

03:05.818 --> 03:07.985
Free interest?
- Ooh.

03:07.987 --> 03:09.086
[laughs]
yes!

03:09.088 --> 03:10.054
I'll have that please.

03:10.056 --> 03:13.558
- Okay, but you'll have
to make a deposit first.

03:13.560 --> 03:14.091
- Oh, of course!

03:14.093 --> 03:18.462
Here's me prize penny
to deposit in a new account.

03:18.464 --> 03:20.698
- Okay, I'll set it right up.

03:20.700 --> 03:21.966
- [normal voice]
wait!

03:21.968 --> 03:23.534
[falsetto]
uh, whatcha doing?

03:23.536 --> 03:25.369
Penny doesn't want
to be crammed in there

03:25.371 --> 03:26.571
With all those other coins.

03:26.573 --> 03:29.373
She wants a money condo
of her own.

03:29.375 --> 03:29.941
- Okay.

03:29.943 --> 03:32.243
You want
a safe deposit box then?

03:32.245 --> 03:32.910
- Oh, yes!

03:32.912 --> 03:34.478
Penny will have one of those.

03:34.480 --> 03:35.746
- Uh, this way, please.

03:35.748 --> 03:37.949
- [plinking tiptoeing]

03:37.951 --> 03:39.383
Wait!

03:39.385 --> 03:43.454
Can I have a moment
with me penny, alone?

03:43.456 --> 03:45.056
- [sighs]
make it quick.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.158
We're closing
in five minutes.

03:47.160 --> 03:48.125
- Oh, penny.

03:48.127 --> 03:49.927
I'm gonna miss you.

03:49.929 --> 03:53.197
[cries]

03:53.199 --> 03:54.398
[sobs]

03:54.400 --> 03:56.767
It's inhuman, I tell you!

03:56.769 --> 03:58.502
Oh, penny, penny.

03:58.504 --> 04:02.740
One last kiss good-bye.

04:02.742 --> 04:05.343
[grunts]
[clothes pop]

04:05.345 --> 04:08.879
[grunting]

04:08.881 --> 04:10.982
It's just you and me now,
little penny.

04:10.984 --> 04:14.185
Yeesh, ooh, it's
a wee bit cramped in here.

04:14.187 --> 04:14.885
[keys jingling]

04:14.887 --> 04:17.154
- Oh, well, that looks secure.

04:17.156 --> 04:19.190
- Whoa!

04:19.192 --> 04:20.925
- Were you people trained
in a barn?

04:20.927 --> 04:22.460
- [gasps]
[heavenly choir vocals]

04:22.462 --> 04:24.462
[gulps]
this can't be true.

04:24.464 --> 04:26.230
[cash register ka-ching]

04:26.232 --> 04:28.899
[sniffs]

04:28.901 --> 04:29.767
- [gasps]

04:29.769 --> 04:30.701
- 'tis true!

04:30.703 --> 04:34.372
I've landed
in money "nir-vanner!"

04:34.374 --> 04:38.509
Me wildest dream's
finally come true!

04:38.511 --> 04:42.046
[laughs wildly]
[cash register ka-ching]

04:42.048 --> 04:45.283
- Mr. Krabs, I'm done
watering down the ketchup.

04:45.285 --> 04:46.317
Did you want me to--

04:46.319 --> 04:48.853
[crickets chirping]

04:48.855 --> 04:51.555
Mr. Krabs?
Mr. Krabs?

04:51.557 --> 04:52.256
Mr. Krabs!

04:52.258 --> 04:54.659
- Would you pipe down!
- Sorry, squidward.

04:54.661 --> 04:57.395
I can't find mr. Krabs,
and he said he'd be right back.

04:57.397 --> 04:59.130
I'm getting
a little concerned.

04:59.132 --> 05:00.298
- That's nice.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.233
And...Interesting.

05:02.235 --> 05:03.601
- I can't take it anymore.

05:03.603 --> 05:05.369
I'm gonna go look for him.

05:05.371 --> 05:06.470
Hold on, mr. Krabs.

05:06.472 --> 05:08.105
I'm coming for you.

05:08.107 --> 05:09.140
[dramatic music]

05:09.142 --> 05:10.941
Mr. Krabs!

05:10.943 --> 05:13.978
[singsong]
mr. Krabs!

05:13.980 --> 05:16.614
Mr. Krabs!

05:16.616 --> 05:19.083
Mr. Krabs!

05:19.085 --> 05:20.351
[squishing footfall]

05:20.353 --> 05:22.820
- Well, time to head home.
Whoo-hoo!

05:22.822 --> 05:24.622
I hope to see each
and every one of you

05:24.624 --> 05:25.723
On the outside.

05:25.725 --> 05:28.659
[grunting]

05:28.661 --> 05:30.194
Wait!
[grunts]

05:30.196 --> 05:31.062
Blimey, I'm locked in!

05:31.064 --> 05:34.565
[grunts] I guess
I'm trapped here all night.

05:34.567 --> 05:37.168
[honk]
with all this moola.

05:37.170 --> 05:40.805
[sighs]
so much moola.

05:43.475 --> 05:44.775
But no one to tell about it!

05:44.777 --> 05:49.413
Time to rustle me up
some friends!

05:49.415 --> 05:50.848
[knock at door]

05:50.850 --> 05:51.949
- Oh, hi, pearl.

05:51.951 --> 05:53.417
Is mr. Krabs here?
- No.

05:53.419 --> 05:55.653
- Pearl, I hate to be the one
to tell you this,

05:55.655 --> 05:56.921
But mr. Krabs is missing!

05:56.923 --> 05:59.323
- Oh, my gosh.
- I know!

05:59.325 --> 06:00.257
- Oh, my gosh.

06:00.259 --> 06:02.259
- Don't worry,
I'll find him.

06:02.261 --> 06:02.827
- Oh, my gosh!

06:02.829 --> 06:06.063
Call him on his cell!
[dial tone]

06:06.065 --> 06:09.533
[gentle jazz music]

06:09.535 --> 06:09.967
♪ ♪

06:09.969 --> 06:12.670
- You look
absolutely stunning tonight,

06:12.672 --> 06:14.472
Mrs. Greenback.

06:14.474 --> 06:15.473
[snaps claw]
waiter!

06:15.475 --> 06:16.774
[assumes french accent]
<i>oui, oui, monsieur.</i>

06:16.776 --> 06:20.010
What can I get you
and the lady tonight?

06:20.012 --> 06:20.778
The lady would like

06:20.780 --> 06:22.980
To start
with a million clams,

06:22.982 --> 06:25.082
A side of investments,

06:25.084 --> 06:27.852
And hold the taxes.

06:27.854 --> 06:28.853
I'll have the same.

06:28.855 --> 06:31.122
But with extra "no taxes."

06:31.124 --> 06:33.958
[sighs]
such a friendly fellow.

06:33.960 --> 06:34.592
Good-looking too.

06:34.594 --> 06:36.894
I'm almost gonna regret
not leaving him a tip.

06:36.896 --> 06:37.962
[cell phone rings]

06:37.964 --> 06:39.397
[beep]
hello.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.132
- Mr. Krabs, are you okay?

06:41.134 --> 06:41.832
- I'm fine, boy!

06:41.834 --> 06:44.001
In fact, I'm dancing
with a beautiful lady!

06:44.003 --> 06:44.735
- Oh, that's nice.

06:44.737 --> 06:47.605
- Yes, and she's made
entirely out of money.

06:47.607 --> 06:48.339
- What? Where are you?

06:48.341 --> 06:51.675
- I'm locked in the bank vault
and having the time of me life!

06:51.677 --> 06:53.677
Oh, and I think
I'm running out of oxygen,

06:53.679 --> 06:55.179
And it's making me
lose my mind.

06:55.181 --> 06:57.581
- I've gotta save mr. Krabs!

06:57.583 --> 06:59.250
Patrick!
[pop]

06:59.252 --> 07:00.718
Patrick, you gotta
help me, buddy!

07:00.720 --> 07:04.722
- [slurps]
- I need to break into a bank.

07:06.591 --> 07:07.291
- What?

07:07.293 --> 07:09.460
Spongebob squarepants.

07:09.462 --> 07:11.829
We have been friends
for a long time.

07:11.831 --> 07:15.900
And you've asked me
to do some <i>crazy</i> things

07:15.902 --> 07:16.700
Over the years.

07:16.702 --> 07:20.171
But breaking into a bank...

07:20.173 --> 07:22.773
Has to be the coolest!

07:22.775 --> 07:25.576
[lilting hawaiian music]

07:25.578 --> 07:27.678
- Ah, this is the life.

07:27.680 --> 07:29.547
Sun, sand and surf.

07:29.549 --> 07:34.618
And, of course,
mrs. Greenback by my side.

07:34.620 --> 07:36.787
What's that?

07:36.789 --> 07:37.988
Oh, don't start on me now.

07:37.990 --> 07:40.424
I'm sure this remote island
has a food source.

07:40.426 --> 07:43.561
Old krabs just hasn't
found it yet, that's all.

07:43.563 --> 07:44.829
I'll just...

07:44.831 --> 07:46.330
[laughs nervously]

07:46.332 --> 07:47.631
So hungry.

07:47.633 --> 07:50.568
[tense music]

07:50.570 --> 07:52.102
- Coast is clear.

07:52.104 --> 07:52.903
What's the plan, buddy?

07:52.905 --> 07:55.840
- Okay, first,
we climb up the walls.

07:55.842 --> 07:58.709
Then, we slide
down the chimney

07:58.711 --> 08:00.311
And eat up
all the milk and cookies

08:00.313 --> 08:01.679
They left out for us!

08:01.681 --> 08:02.580
- Well, I don't see a chimney,

08:02.582 --> 08:04.815
But we could try getting in
through a roof vent.

08:04.817 --> 08:07.384
If only we had a way
to scale this wall.

08:07.386 --> 08:11.822
- Luckily, I brought
the bank break-in kit.

08:11.824 --> 08:14.758
Uh...

08:14.760 --> 08:15.626
How about this?

08:15.628 --> 08:16.527
- A bunch of old shoelaces?

08:16.529 --> 08:20.731
- It's as close as I'll ever get
to having shoes.

08:20.733 --> 08:22.466
- I wish we had
something stronger,

08:22.468 --> 08:25.636
But this'll have to do.

08:27.205 --> 08:31.742
[screaming]
[rope snapping]

08:31.744 --> 08:33.744
- Hey, spongebob,
I got an idea!

08:33.746 --> 08:37.615
Let's use this grappling hook.

08:37.616 --> 08:39.049
[hook clanks]

08:39.051 --> 08:40.484
[tense music]

08:40.486 --> 08:44.321
[plinking tiptoeing]

08:44.556 --> 08:47.424
- This vent will surely
lead us straight to mr. Krabs.

08:47.426 --> 08:48.993
- Let's get him!

08:48.995 --> 08:49.693
[grunting]

08:49.695 --> 08:51.595
[screaming]
[thumping]

08:51.597 --> 08:53.864
[crash]
[screaming, thumping]

08:53.866 --> 08:56.433
[crash]
[screaming, thumping]

08:56.435 --> 08:58.235
[whoosh, crash]

08:58.237 --> 09:00.237
Cool!
Let's do that again!

09:00.239 --> 09:02.473
- Not now, patrick,
we're running out of time.

09:02.475 --> 09:03.340
And, more importantly,

09:03.342 --> 09:05.242
Mr. Krabs is running out
of oxygen.

09:05.244 --> 09:06.410
- [plinking tiptoeing]

09:06.412 --> 09:07.678
[jabbering]

09:07.680 --> 09:10.781
So hungry.

09:10.783 --> 09:12.283
Oh, why did I come

09:12.285 --> 09:14.785
To this
uninhabitable-ble island?

09:14.787 --> 09:16.887
Why did I do it?

09:16.889 --> 09:18.489
What? Huh?

09:18.491 --> 09:22.893
Why did I say all that
to mrs. Greenback?

09:22.895 --> 09:24.228
I-I miss her.

09:24.230 --> 09:26.764
Why isn't she--
mrs. Greenback!

09:26.766 --> 09:29.300
[claws clacking]
where can she be?

09:29.302 --> 09:30.801
What have I done?

09:30.803 --> 09:32.469
Oh. Oh, mrs. Greenback!

09:32.471 --> 09:34.905
Mrs. Greenback!
You're okay!

09:34.907 --> 09:36.807
I-I was so worried.

09:36.809 --> 09:37.675
I'm so sorry.

09:37.677 --> 09:39.843
You must never run away
like that again.

09:39.845 --> 09:40.511
[wind whooshes]

09:40.513 --> 09:42.613
What's this?
[screams]

09:42.615 --> 09:43.547
Little miss!

09:43.549 --> 09:44.381
What the neptune?

09:44.383 --> 09:46.283
- [inhaling loudly]
- a slimy money dragon!

09:46.285 --> 09:49.219
You're not sucking away
me fortune without a fight!

09:49.221 --> 09:50.287
[punches]

09:50.289 --> 09:50.854
[vacuum sucking]

09:50.856 --> 09:55.392
Give me back mrs. Greenback,
you beast!

09:55.394 --> 09:56.093
- Patrick, you ready?

09:56.095 --> 09:59.930
- This lock won't know
what hit it.

09:59.932 --> 10:02.199
- Uh, careful, patrick.

10:02.201 --> 10:03.233
Use finesse.

10:03.235 --> 10:04.001
- Oh, right.

10:04.003 --> 10:06.403
[clank]
I'll use the finesse.

10:06.405 --> 10:10.140
[engine revving,
tool clanks]

10:10.142 --> 10:11.709
- Good morning, gentlemen.

10:11.711 --> 10:12.910
[screaming]

10:12.912 --> 10:14.678
- We've been rumbled!

10:14.680 --> 10:15.746
Run! Scatter!

10:15.748 --> 10:17.348
Scamper! Save yourself!

10:17.350 --> 10:19.516
- What's all this about?

10:19.518 --> 10:23.087
[tense music]

10:23.089 --> 10:24.922
- Well...

10:24.924 --> 10:26.890
- May I help you
with anything, sir?

10:26.892 --> 10:28.959
- Ah, yes, I need
to make a withdrawal.

10:28.961 --> 10:31.428
I need to withdraw
one mr. Krabs.

10:31.430 --> 10:33.797
- I assure you,
mr. Squarepants,

10:33.799 --> 10:36.400
We received no such deposit.

10:36.402 --> 10:37.101
[lock clanking]

10:37.103 --> 10:38.869
[door hinge creaks]
[gasps]

10:38.871 --> 10:42.072
- I've got you now,
money-sucker!

10:42.074 --> 10:44.575
[vacuum sucking]
that does it, lizard breath!

10:44.577 --> 10:47.111
It's you or me now.

10:47.113 --> 10:48.879
Just you and me.

10:48.881 --> 10:53.884
[grunting]

10:53.886 --> 10:55.252
Yah!
[sucking stops]

10:55.254 --> 10:57.688
[evil laugh]

10:57.690 --> 11:00.924
[hysterical laugh]

11:00.926 --> 11:04.728
Ooh!
♪ I conquered the money dragon

11:04.730 --> 11:05.829
Victory! Whoo!

11:05.831 --> 11:07.097
- [teeth chattering]

11:07.099 --> 11:08.766
Security!

11:08.768 --> 11:10.267
[keys jingling]

11:10.269 --> 11:12.369
[musical splatting]

11:12.371 --> 11:16.273
And don't forget your...
[sighs] deposit.

11:16.275 --> 11:17.441
[penny clinks]

11:17.443 --> 11:18.876
- You know, boyo,

11:18.878 --> 11:20.344
Through this whole ordeal,

11:20.346 --> 11:23.313
I've learned
a little something about greed.

11:23.315 --> 11:25.349
A little something
about isolation.

11:25.351 --> 11:29.119
[chuckles] even a little
something about love.

11:29.121 --> 11:31.422
And you know what I realize,
through it all?

11:31.424 --> 11:34.158
- That you can't
put a price on freedom?

11:34.160 --> 11:35.359
- Barnacles, no, boy!

11:35.361 --> 11:40.030
I realize that they didn't
pay interest on me deposit!

11:40.032 --> 11:41.432
Hey, you cheapskates!

11:41.434 --> 11:42.900
Gimme me interest!

11:42.902 --> 11:44.268
[penny clinks]

11:44.270 --> 11:45.202
Well!

11:45.204 --> 11:46.637
What do you know?

11:46.639 --> 11:48.505
I doubled me money.

11:48.507 --> 11:51.375
[chortles]

11:53.278 --> 11:57.014
[lilting ukulele music]

11:57.016 --> 12:03.587
♪ ♪

12:03.589 --> 12:06.690
- Order up!

12:06.692 --> 12:08.258
- Here.
[clank]

12:08.260 --> 12:09.493
- Goo!

12:09.495 --> 12:10.494
- Hey, there.

12:10.496 --> 12:11.595
- [raspberry]

12:11.597 --> 12:12.663
Num, num!

12:12.665 --> 12:17.000
- Aw, does baby
want a krabby patty, hmm?

12:17.002 --> 12:18.302
- Aw.

12:18.304 --> 12:23.440
- Baby's first krabby patty.
[sniffles]

12:26.711 --> 12:29.213
- That diabolical fiend!

12:29.215 --> 12:31.482
- I can't believe
this is working!

12:31.484 --> 12:34.585
It's like taking candy
from a baby--

12:34.587 --> 12:35.519
<i>With</i> a baby.

12:35.521 --> 12:40.157
- Stop right there,
you thievin' infant!

12:40.159 --> 12:44.428
[mechanical ratcheting]

12:44.430 --> 12:46.597
[growls]

12:46.599 --> 12:47.731
- Yi-eeh! That's harsh.

12:47.733 --> 12:50.234
- So you thought you could
pull a fast one, eh?

12:50.236 --> 12:53.403
Now, come out of there,
you little pest!

12:53.405 --> 12:55.139
[grunting]

12:55.141 --> 12:56.540
- [gasps]
what's he doing?

12:56.542 --> 12:59.710
You leave
that poor baby alone!

12:59.712 --> 13:00.511
- Okay.

13:00.513 --> 13:04.414
I guess we're gonna have
to do this the hard way.

13:04.416 --> 13:05.682
- Mr. Krabs, no!

13:05.684 --> 13:06.683
Don't do it!

13:06.685 --> 13:09.353
[grunts]
[rip]

13:09.355 --> 13:11.455
- Ooh! Oh...
[thump]

13:11.457 --> 13:12.956
- Oh!
[thump]

13:12.958 --> 13:14.658
- Oh, calm down!

13:14.660 --> 13:16.460
It's just plankton.

13:16.462 --> 13:17.327
[pop]

13:17.329 --> 13:20.597
- See?
- Uh...Goo-goo?

13:20.599 --> 13:21.999
- How dare you!

13:22.001 --> 13:23.867
You toyed with our emotions!

13:23.869 --> 13:25.402
[squish]
- ow.

13:25.404 --> 13:26.970
- Face it, plankton.

13:26.972 --> 13:28.405
You're never gonna win.

13:28.407 --> 13:32.576
I'll always be
one step...Ahead.

13:32.578 --> 13:33.477
[chuckles]

13:33.479 --> 13:37.347
Now, why don't you go back
to where you came from,

13:37.349 --> 13:38.348
You little brat.

13:38.350 --> 13:39.383
[whoosh, crash]

13:39.385 --> 13:40.684
All: [gasp]

13:40.686 --> 13:41.285
- Uh-oh.

13:41.287 --> 13:45.222
- You monster!
- How dare you!

13:45.957 --> 13:47.758
- [wailing]

13:47.760 --> 13:52.763
- Aww, diddums fail
to get a krabby patty again?

13:52.765 --> 13:53.630
[horn honks]

13:53.632 --> 13:55.165
- Stop patronizing me!

13:55.167 --> 13:58.902
Why does every single plan
fall apart?

13:58.904 --> 14:00.871
It's just a stupid sandwich!

14:00.873 --> 14:03.373
I tell you,
it's wearing me down!

14:03.375 --> 14:06.343
- You need
to stop obsessing over it.

14:06.345 --> 14:08.812
Relax. Get a hobby
or something.

14:08.814 --> 14:11.248
- I hate to admit it,
computer wife,

14:11.250 --> 14:12.816
But you're probably right.

14:12.818 --> 14:13.417
I need something

14:13.419 --> 14:16.854
To take my mind off
that blasted secret formula

14:16.856 --> 14:17.721
For a while.

14:17.723 --> 14:19.156
But what?
- I know.

14:19.158 --> 14:22.793
How about taking care
of an inferior life-form?

14:22.795 --> 14:24.261
- You mean a pet?

14:24.263 --> 14:27.164
That's a great idea!

14:27.166 --> 14:28.732
But how will I find a pet

14:28.734 --> 14:30.834
That fits
my dynamic personality?

14:30.836 --> 14:31.768
- Plankton.
- [screams]

14:31.770 --> 14:34.404
- I have the perfect solution
to your problem.

14:34.406 --> 14:35.239
- Spongebob?

14:35.241 --> 14:37.774
How could <i>you</i>
possibly help me?

14:37.776 --> 14:40.077
- You should try
the local animal shelter.

14:40.079 --> 14:42.412
That's where I found
my gary.

14:42.414 --> 14:42.980
- Oh, yeah?

14:42.982 --> 14:46.817
Perhaps you're
on to something there.

14:46.819 --> 14:48.418
- Here it is.

14:48.420 --> 14:49.786
The bikini bottom
animal shelter.

14:49.788 --> 14:52.322
[pets barking]
your perfect pet awaits.

14:52.324 --> 14:54.992
Now, if you just listen
to your heart,

14:54.994 --> 14:57.160
You'll be able
to pick out the right pet

14:57.162 --> 14:58.228
As soon as you see it.

14:58.230 --> 15:01.331
[barking continues]
- hmm. Too big.

15:01.333 --> 15:02.833
Too sloppy.

15:02.835 --> 15:05.168
- Duh.
- Too stupid.

15:05.170 --> 15:06.603
- Hi, spongebob.

15:06.605 --> 15:07.571
- Hey, patrick.

15:07.573 --> 15:09.473
Oh! Oh!
What about this one?

15:09.475 --> 15:11.375
- Are you kidding me?

15:11.377 --> 15:12.676
Algae on a rock?

15:12.678 --> 15:14.878
I want a pet,
not a plant.

15:14.880 --> 15:16.580
It's no use.

15:16.582 --> 15:17.347
- [snarls]

15:17.349 --> 15:19.149
- There's nothing for me here.

15:19.151 --> 15:20.083
[screams]

15:20.085 --> 15:21.351
- Oh, no!
Plankton!

15:21.353 --> 15:23.921
- You know,
I can't say I'm surprised.

15:23.923 --> 15:27.791
- [barking]

15:27.793 --> 15:29.726
[growls, chomps]

15:29.728 --> 15:31.261
- [screams]

15:31.263 --> 15:32.195
- [barks]

15:32.197 --> 15:35.399
- Hey there, little guy.

15:35.401 --> 15:38.602
- [barks]
- looks like we have a winner.

15:38.604 --> 15:40.304
- Oh, so cute!

15:40.306 --> 15:41.238
Whatcha gonna call him?

15:41.240 --> 15:43.807
He looks like a "spot" to me.

15:43.809 --> 15:44.675
- [chomps, growling]

15:44.677 --> 15:48.578
- That name provokes
a violent reaction.

15:48.580 --> 15:51.148
Spot it is!

15:51.150 --> 15:54.551
- [barks, panting]

15:54.553 --> 15:56.253
- Well, spot.

15:56.255 --> 15:57.921
I'm your new owner,

15:57.923 --> 16:02.893
So shower me
with love and affection.

16:02.895 --> 16:03.393
Karen,

16:03.395 --> 16:05.896
It's not giving me
unconditional love.

16:05.898 --> 16:07.230
I think it's defective.

16:07.232 --> 16:10.067
- You're gonna have
to train him to do that.

16:10.069 --> 16:11.501
- I train him?

16:11.503 --> 16:13.403
[sighs]
I'll give it a shot.

16:13.405 --> 16:14.538
All right, spot.

16:14.540 --> 16:17.007
Let's start
with something easy.

16:17.009 --> 16:20.277
Stay.

16:20.279 --> 16:22.346
Good boy.
Now sit.

16:22.348 --> 16:24.548
[squishing]

16:24.550 --> 16:25.916
Very good!

16:25.918 --> 16:27.918
Now roll over.

16:27.920 --> 16:30.120
- [barks]
- excellent!

16:30.122 --> 16:31.288
Now shake.

16:31.290 --> 16:34.091
[rumbling, clattering]

16:34.093 --> 16:34.524
Wow!

16:34.526 --> 16:36.460
That's one mean shake
you got there.

16:36.462 --> 16:39.796
I think we should burn off
some of that extra energy.

16:39.798 --> 16:43.500
Would you like
to go walkies?

16:43.502 --> 16:47.137
I'll assume that's a yes.

16:47.139 --> 16:48.071
March!

16:48.073 --> 16:51.141
- [barking]

16:51.143 --> 16:54.411
- [whistles cheerfully]

16:54.413 --> 16:58.415
[whistling peters out]

16:58.417 --> 17:00.484
[panting]

17:00.486 --> 17:01.151
Phew!

17:01.153 --> 17:03.754
We must've walked for miles.

17:03.756 --> 17:05.722
[squishes]

17:05.723 --> 17:08.892
I guess our legs
are too short for walkies.

17:08.894 --> 17:13.563
How about
a nice round of fetch?

17:13.565 --> 17:17.233
[grunting]

17:17.236 --> 17:18.367
Fetch!

17:18.369 --> 17:20.337
[splat]

17:20.339 --> 17:21.304
[snap]

17:21.306 --> 17:22.439
[screams]

17:22.441 --> 17:23.373
Oh, no.

17:23.375 --> 17:24.040
What have I done?

17:24.042 --> 17:27.377
I'm a terrible pet owner!
Terrible!

17:27.378 --> 17:28.345
Karen!

17:28.347 --> 17:30.313
We're gonna need another spot!

17:30.315 --> 17:33.283
[squishing]

17:33.285 --> 17:34.151
- [barks]

17:34.153 --> 17:36.386
- Nice rebound, spot!

17:36.388 --> 17:40.590
You know,
I get squished a lot too.

17:40.592 --> 17:41.191
[sniffles]

17:41.193 --> 17:44.061
I hope nobody saw
that emotional outburst.

17:44.063 --> 17:46.396
All: Aw.

17:46.398 --> 17:49.366
- Shoo!

17:49.368 --> 17:50.167
Okay, spot.

17:50.169 --> 17:52.636
Today, you'll learn
how to be an attack pet

17:52.638 --> 17:55.205
To guard the chum bucket
from intruders.

17:55.207 --> 17:58.909
Now, spot,
pretend I'm a burglar.

17:58.911 --> 17:59.776
Attack!

17:59.778 --> 18:01.378
- [whimpers]

18:01.380 --> 18:03.180
- You're not getting this?

18:03.182 --> 18:04.081
Come at me!

18:04.083 --> 18:07.417
Uh-oh,
losing balance.

18:07.419 --> 18:08.752
A little help?

18:08.754 --> 18:10.720
- [boings]

18:10.722 --> 18:11.588
[barks]

18:11.590 --> 18:12.456
- On second thought,

18:12.458 --> 18:14.124
What do I need
a guard dog for?

18:14.126 --> 18:16.126
I can't even <i>give</i> chum away.

18:16.128 --> 18:19.329
What I really need
is a retriever.

18:19.331 --> 18:21.031
This is your target.

18:21.033 --> 18:25.068
I want you to retrieve
the krabby patty.

18:25.070 --> 18:26.837
Now, security is tight,

18:26.839 --> 18:29.005
So I've devised a pl--

18:29.007 --> 18:29.873
Wait!

18:29.875 --> 18:31.208
Where are you going?

18:31.210 --> 18:33.243
You're not ready!

18:33.245 --> 18:37.647
- [sniffing]

18:40.151 --> 18:41.351
[pop]

18:41.353 --> 18:45.155
[sniffing]

18:45.157 --> 18:48.091
- [humming cheerfully]

18:48.093 --> 18:51.695
- I'd like a large...

18:51.697 --> 18:52.529
What was that?

18:52.531 --> 18:55.065
- Didn't see it,
don't care.

18:55.067 --> 18:55.899
- [snoring]

18:55.901 --> 18:57.734
[thump]
- [barking]

18:57.736 --> 18:59.603
- Holy plot twist!

18:59.605 --> 19:00.537
It's a krabby patty!

19:00.539 --> 19:04.174
It's...A miracle!
[heavenly choir vocals]

19:04.176 --> 19:06.910
Karen, look
at what spot brought home.

19:06.912 --> 19:08.445
- That's wonderful!

19:08.447 --> 19:10.046
Spot deserves a reward.

19:10.048 --> 19:12.482
- He can have
anything he wants,

19:12.484 --> 19:14.217
Up to half my kingdom--

19:14.219 --> 19:15.152
Uh, laboratory.

19:15.154 --> 19:17.954
- I think he wants
your krabby patty.

19:17.956 --> 19:19.656
- [panting]

19:19.658 --> 19:22.659
[chomps]
- noo!

19:22.661 --> 19:23.160
No!

19:23.162 --> 19:25.495
You've been a very bad amoeba!

19:25.497 --> 19:26.096
Bad amoeba!

19:26.098 --> 19:29.065
I'm afraid you'll have
to be punished.

19:29.067 --> 19:30.700
You need a time out.

19:30.702 --> 19:32.936
I'm just gonna tie you up
out here

19:32.938 --> 19:34.804
Until you learn
to behave.

19:34.806 --> 19:37.374
Shouldn't take
more than five minutes.

19:37.376 --> 19:39.009
- [whimpers, yaps]

19:39.011 --> 19:40.076
- Aw...

19:40.078 --> 19:42.612
No, no,
I must be strong.

19:42.614 --> 19:45.615
- [whimpers]

19:45.617 --> 19:47.150
- I can't do it.

19:47.152 --> 19:50.353
[tender music]
spot, I'm sorry. I--

19:50.355 --> 19:51.755
[music peters out]

19:51.757 --> 19:53.924
[tense music]

19:53.926 --> 19:55.759
Spot!

19:55.761 --> 19:56.626
He's gone.

19:56.628 --> 19:58.361
[crying]
where is he?

19:58.363 --> 20:00.096
Spot! Come back!

20:00.098 --> 20:02.666
[sobbing] spot!
Come back!

20:02.668 --> 20:04.768
I've got to find him.

20:04.770 --> 20:05.869
All: Aw.

20:05.871 --> 20:08.838
- Don't any of you have jobs?

20:08.840 --> 20:09.539
Spot!

20:09.541 --> 20:12.909
Spot!
Where are you, spot!

20:12.911 --> 20:13.877
[sobbing]

20:13.879 --> 20:16.112
- Why, plankton,
what's wrong?

20:16.114 --> 20:17.480
- I lost spot.

20:17.482 --> 20:18.982
- That's terrible!

20:18.984 --> 20:20.383
Gary lost me once.

20:20.385 --> 20:23.286
I was cold, alone, starving.

20:23.288 --> 20:24.788
It was the worst eight minutes
of my life.

20:24.790 --> 20:28.692
Come on, plankton,
let's find your pet.

20:28.694 --> 20:29.492
Lost pet!

20:29.494 --> 20:31.595
Anyone seen this lost pet?

20:31.597 --> 20:32.896
Lost pet emergency!

20:32.898 --> 20:34.965
Be on the lookout
for a lost pet!

20:34.967 --> 20:38.168
Pardon me, sir.
Have you seen this amoeba?

20:38.170 --> 20:41.471
- You mean that little speck?
- No.

20:41.473 --> 20:45.475
<i>That</i> little speck.
- Is this him?

20:45.477 --> 20:47.644
- No, that's a piece of gum.

20:47.646 --> 20:49.579
- Gum?

20:49.581 --> 20:54.117
I've been looking everywhere
for this.

20:54.119 --> 20:56.519
If I was lookin'
for a lost pet,

20:56.521 --> 20:59.089
I'd try the animal shelter.

20:59.091 --> 21:00.223
- Of course!

21:00.225 --> 21:02.959
Both: The shelter!

21:04.695 --> 21:06.329
- I think it's closed
for the night.

21:06.331 --> 21:07.330
[door clanks]

21:07.332 --> 21:08.999
Ooh, it's dark in here.

21:09.001 --> 21:11.101
I'll find a light switch.

21:11.103 --> 21:12.402
Aha!
[switch clicks]

21:12.404 --> 21:15.905
[metallic clank]
no, that's not it.

21:15.907 --> 21:17.140
[switch clicks]

21:17.142 --> 21:19.476
Aha! Found the lights.

21:19.478 --> 21:20.443
- Uh, spongebob?

21:20.445 --> 21:23.179
What was that first switch for?

21:23.181 --> 21:24.347
- I dunno.

21:24.349 --> 21:26.049
I think it unlocks the pens?

21:26.051 --> 21:26.716
- I thought so.

21:26.718 --> 21:29.552
Because now
the animals are loose!

21:29.554 --> 21:30.186
[animals shriek]

21:30.188 --> 21:32.489
- Spongebob?
- Run for it?

21:32.491 --> 21:33.890
- Yep.

21:33.892 --> 21:35.025
- [panting]

21:35.027 --> 21:38.561
[animals shrieking]

21:40.331 --> 21:41.231
[panting]

21:41.233 --> 21:42.065
I think we lost 'em.

21:42.067 --> 21:44.501
- Spongebob,
before we're torn to shreds,

21:44.503 --> 21:47.904
I'd like to thank you
for helping me look for spot.

21:47.906 --> 21:49.539
- Aw, it was nothing.

21:49.541 --> 21:50.707
Hey, speaking of spots.

21:50.709 --> 21:53.076
Did you always have
a double pupil?

21:53.078 --> 21:55.011
- A double what?

21:55.013 --> 21:56.379
[snap]

21:56.381 --> 21:57.580
[pop]
spot!

21:57.582 --> 21:59.949
[dramatic music]
thank entropy you're safe!

21:59.951 --> 22:02.819
You were hiding
on my optical cornea

22:02.821 --> 22:04.087
The whole time!

22:04.089 --> 22:06.723
You sneaky little amoeba, you.

22:06.725 --> 22:08.358
- [barks]

22:08.360 --> 22:09.559
- [laughs]

22:09.561 --> 22:11.728
- Aw, I'm glad
you found spot.

22:11.730 --> 22:12.395
[animals shrieking]

22:12.397 --> 22:16.566
Unfortunately,
the animals found us too.

22:16.568 --> 22:17.200
- Good-bye, spot.

22:17.202 --> 22:20.403
I guess this is the end
of the road for us.

22:20.405 --> 22:21.571
- [growls]

22:21.573 --> 22:22.772
[barks]

22:22.774 --> 22:24.140
- Spot, no!

22:24.142 --> 22:26.009
- [barking]

22:26.011 --> 22:27.577
[laughter]

22:27.579 --> 22:31.948
[snarling]

22:34.018 --> 22:35.985
[barking]

22:35.987 --> 22:38.988
[dramatic music]

22:38.990 --> 22:40.824
♪

22:40.826 --> 22:43.493
[growls, barks]

22:44.362 --> 22:46.229
- Wow, spot!
You saved us!

22:46.231 --> 22:48.531
- I taught him
everything he knows!

22:48.533 --> 22:51.468
- [barks]

22:53.471 --> 22:56.706
[lilting ukulele music]

22:56.708 --> 23:05.014
♪ ♪
